'''Carlos Alberto Cheppi''' (born 1955 in [[Mar del Plata]]) is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] diplomat who currently serves as Argentina's [[ambassador]] to [[Venezuela]].

Cheppi graduated in [[agronomy]] from the [[National University of Mar del Plata]] in 1981 and joined the [[National Agricultural Technology Institute]] two years later. He rose to become the institute's president in 2003. He replaced [[Javier de Urquiza]] as Minister of Agriculture in July 2008 during the [[2008 Argentine government conflict with the agricultural sector|Argentine government's conflict with the agricultural sector]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Quién es Carlos Cheppi, el sucesor de De Urquiza |url= http://www.perfil.com/politica/Quien-es-Carlos-Cheppi-el-sucesor-de-De-Urquiza-20080721-0008.html|language=Spanish |publisher= ''[[Perfil]]''|date=21 July 2008|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref> After leaving the post the following year, Cheppi was appointed ambassador plenipotentiary in the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Worship|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]]. In 2011 he stood unsuccessfully for mayor of Mar del Plata. He was appointed ambassador to Venezuela in December 2011.<ref>{{cite news |title= Carlos Cheppi será el embajador en Venezuela |url= http://www.infobae.com/2011/12/09/621393-carlos-cheppi-sera-el-embajador-venezuela|language=Spanish |publisher= infobae|date=9 December 2011|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

